### Cause

Deserialization using Builder does not work with `readerForUpdating`, as suggested [by Jan Rieke](https://stackoverflow.com/users/10026074/jan-rieke),
&gt; updating an existing instance can never be achieved using a builder: builders always create new instances

### Details

When using `@Jacksonized`, 
&gt;Configure Jackson to use the builder for deserialization using @JsonDeserialize(builder=Foobar.FoobarBuilder[Impl].class) on the class (where Foobar is the name of the annotated class).

we tell Jackson to deserialize using the builder.

With the error message and referring to [jackson 2.15 BuilderBasedDeserializer][1], 
```java
    @Override
    public Object deserialize(JsonParser p, DeserializationContext ctxt,
    		Object value) throws IOException
    {
        // 26-Oct-2016, tatu: I cannot see any of making this actually
        //    work correctly, so let&#39;s indicate problem right away
        JavaType valueType = _targetType;
        // Did they try to give us builder?
        Class&lt;?&gt; builderRawType = handledType();
        Class&lt;?&gt; instRawType = value.getClass();
        if (builderRawType.isAssignableFrom(instRawType)) {
            return ctxt.reportBadDefinition(valueType, String.format(
                    &quot;Deserialization of %s by passing existing Builder (%s) instance not supported&quot;,
                    valueType, builderRawType.getName()));
        }
        return ctxt.reportBadDefinition(valueType, String.format(
                &quot;Deserialization of %s by passing existing instance (of %s) not supported&quot;,
                valueType, instRawType.getName()));
    }
```
We can see this feature is not ready for use from the comment.

### Workaround
1. Do not use @Jacksonized
2. Use other library like [Spring BeanUtils][2] to update the values.


  [1]: https://github.com/FasterXML/jackson-databind/blob/2.15/src/main/java/com/fasterxml/jackson/databind/deser/BuilderBasedDeserializer.java#L252
  [2]: https://docs.spring.io/spring-framework/docs/current/javadoc-api/org/springframework/beans/BeanUtils.html

