The `PageFactory` class resides among other classes such as `SlowLoadableComponent`, `FluentWait`, and `WebDriverWait` in the `selenium-support` library. Consider these classes as tools at your disposal; it&#39;s up to you whether you choose to use them or not.

Regarding `PageFactory`: Interestingly, Simon Stewart (Selenium project lead) admits that it was not the best idea to make it available to the public, as a result almost everybody is using it.
For reference:
https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=gyfUpOysIF8&amp;t=1541s
https://twitter.com/shs96c/status/880809924607057920 

There are many ways to work around PageFactory and still use Page Object model for abstracting your domain, but if you still intend to use it in Kotlin, then make sure to use `lateinit var` for your `WebElement`s: 

    @FindBy(id = &quot;boligLink&quot;)
    lateinit var boliglink: WebElement

And use `MutableList` instead of `List` to avoid `UninitializedPropertyAccessException` at runtime:

    @FindBy(className = &quot;image&quot;)
    lateinit var companyNames: MutableList&lt;WebElement&gt;

