In this solution, I&#39;ve split the input string by `,` and using `Arrays.stream` create a `Stream&lt;String&gt;`. Then, I&#39;ve used `Collectors.groupingBy` to create a map with year as the key and with a *mapping* collector extract the month (as an Integer) and collect them into a `TreeSet` (to collect the months in ascending order).
```
Map&lt;String, Set&lt;Integer&gt;&gt; yearToMonths = Arrays.stream(str.split(&quot;,&quot;))
        .collect(Collectors.groupingBy(s -&gt; s.substring(0, 4),
                Collectors.mapping(s -&gt; Integer.parseInt(s.substring(4)),
                        Collectors.toCollection(TreeSet::new))));
```
With this temporary result, we again stream on the map and by using `Collectors.toMap` build the final map where we take the value (`Set&lt;Integer&gt;`) and join them as a string by `,`.
```
Map&lt;String, String&gt; result = yearToMonths.entrySet()
        .stream()
        .collect(Collectors.toMap(Map.Entry::getKey, e -&gt; e.getValue()
                .stream()
                .map(String::valueOf)
                .collect(Collectors.joining(&quot;,&quot;))));

result.forEach((key, value) -&gt; System.out.println(&quot;[Key] : &quot; + key + &quot; [Value] : &quot; + value));
```

---

If you are beginner and find it difficult to understand Java streams and Collectors, here it a beginner-friendly approach.

    Map&lt;String, Set&lt;Integer&gt;&gt; yearToMonths = new HashMap&lt;&gt;();
