    for (int i = 0; i &lt; lst.length; i++) {
        String year = lst[i].substring(0, 4);
        Integer month = Integer.parseInt(lst[i].substring(4));
        if (!yearToMonths.containsKey(year)) {
            yearToMonths.put(year, new TreeSet&lt;&gt;());
        }
        yearToMonths.get(year)
               .add(month);
    }
    for (Map.Entry&lt;String, Set&lt;Integer&gt;&gt; entry : yearToMonths.entrySet()) {
        String year = entry.getKey();
        Set&lt;Integer&gt; months = entry.getValue();
        StringJoiner stringJoiner = new StringJoiner(&quot;,&quot;);
        for (Integer month : months) {
            stringJoiner.add(String.valueOf(month));
        }
        result.put(year, stringJoiner.toString());
    }
  

I&#39;ve used a `StringJoiner` to join the elements of the Set into a String (rather than a `StringBuilder`) as it will be easier to avoid adding a `,` at the end.

